================================================================================
CODE STRUCTURE
================================================================================

FILES
-----
scoring/model.py: XGBoost training and prediction
scoring/shap_explain.py: SHAP explainability wrapper

KEY CLASSES
-----------
CreditScoreModel:
  - __init__(): Initialize model structure
  - train(): Train on synthetic data
  - predict(wallet_data): Get score 0-1000
  - predict_proba(wallet_data): Get default probability 0-1
  - get_feature_importance(): Get XGBoost feature weights

SHAPExplainer:
  - __init__(): Initialize explainer
  - _get_explainer(): Lazy-load SHAP TreeExplainer
  - explain(wallet_data): Get SHAP values per feature

GLOBAL INSTANCES
----------------
_model: Singleton CreditScoreModel (lazy-loaded)
_explainer: Singleton SHAPExplainer (lazy-loaded)

WHY SINGLETONS?
---------------
- Model training is expensive (1 second)
- Only need one model in memory
- Shared across all API requests
- Lazy loading delays cost until first use


================================================================================
USAGE EXAMPLES
================================================================================

BASIC USAGE
-----------
from scoring.model import get_model
from scoring.shap_explain import explain_score

# Get model (trains on first call)
model = get_model()

# Prepare wallet features
wallet_features = {
    "repayment": 85,
    "wallet_activity": 78,
    "defi": 65,
    "dao": 55,
    "rwa": 45,
    "income": 80,
}

# Get credit score
credit_score, sub_scores = model.predict(wallet_features)
print(f"Credit Score: {credit_score}")  # 750

# Get default probability
default_prob = model.predict_proba(wallet_features)
print(f"Default Probability: {default_prob:.2%}")  # 5.2%

# Get SHAP explanation
shap_values = explain_score(wallet_features)
print(f"Feature Contributions: {shap_values}")

INTEGRATION WITH AGENTS
-----------------------
The Credit Agent uses the model:

from scoring.model import get_model
from scoring.shap_explain import explain_score

def credit_agent(state):
    wallet_features = extract_features(state["wallet_address"])
    
    model = get_model()
    credit_score, sub_scores = model.predict(wallet_features)
    shap_breakdown = explain_score(wallet_features)
    
    return {
        **state,
        "credit_score": credit_score,
        "sub_scores": sub_scores,
        "shap_breakdown": shap_breakdown,
    }


